<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--GracelandPostal     11-01 0098</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Graceland Postal,0101</SECOND>
<HEAD>Presley's Mansion Gets Postal Station</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Return to sender, address unknown'' will
be a phrase coming from Elvis Presley's Graceland mansion, but it
won't be set to music.
   The Postal Service has given Graceland final approval to operate
a postal station in a nearby visitor center. The station will be
operated under contract with the Postal Service and will open
officially later this month.
   Everything mailed there will be postmarked Graceland Contract
Station.
   The mansion is a tourist attraction that has had 650,000
visitors this year. Presley died there in 1977.
</TEXT>
