<SECOND>PM-Scarfo Shot, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0514,0435</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mob Leader's Son Shot in Restaurant</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 3 grafs to UPDATE with condition, CLARIFY that victim
is not Scarfo's only son. PICKS UP 4th graf pvs, `The gunman ...'</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By A.J. HOSTETLER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A son of Philadelphia mob boss Nicodemo
``Little Nicky'' Scarfo was shot and wounded at an Italian
restaurant in what a prosecutor said may have been an attempt to
punish the elder Scarfo.
   A man in a yellow Halloween mask and black clothes Tuesday night
walked up to Nicodemo Scarfo Jr., 24, as he dined at Dante and
Luigi's and opened fire, apparently dropping his gun on the
pavement as he fled, police said.
   Scarfo was hit at least four times, once in the neck and the
left arm and in each side of his chest, and was in critical but
stable condition today at Thomas Jefferson University Hospital,
hospital spokesman Steve Brown said.
   The gunman ``was like greased lightning,'' said Joseph Oberman,
who was dining in the restaurant's main room. ``He came in and out
of the door.''
   ``After the shot, nobody moved,'' Oberman said.
   But another diner, Fran Tosconi, said, ``The dining room was in
chaos.''
   Assistant U.S. Attorney Joel Friedman said the shooting may have
been aimed at the elder Scarfo for failing to keep some mobsters
from becoming informants. He is serving a 69-year sentence
racketeering at the federal prison in Marion, Ill.
   ``There would be many out there that would wish to punish Scarfo
for the lack of discipline within his family,'' Friedman said.
   Friedman speculated the shooting was not part of a struggle for
control of the Philadelphia-southern New Jersey mob triggered by
the 1980 slaying of mob boss Angelo Bruno. At least 24 men have
been killed in that war.
   ``Many of the important members and leaders of the La Cosa
Nostra are currently cooperating and testififying,'' and some major
mob figures have been convicted, Friedman said. ``That could be
deemed an embarrassing situation for Nicodemo Scarfo as the
leader.''
   The elder Scarfo has been imprisoned since his indictment in
1986 in a $1 million extortion attempt. He was convicted in that
case and later on a murder charge.
   Until his sentencing with 16 others last April, the elder Scarfo
was considered the leader of organized crime in the area.
   The younger Scarfo has had several brushes with the law but none
in connection with the mob.
   Police said he apparently was shot with a semi-automatic version
of the MAC-10 machine pistol.
</TEXT>
