<HEAD>US Assails Violence in El Salvador</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The State Department on Wednesday denounced
terrorist attacks on civilian targets in El Salvador that left 10
people dead and dozens injured.
   In one incident, three people, including an American were
injured in a bombing at the office of a group that represents
families of the victims of violence in El Salvador.
   Subsequently, 10 union activists were killed and 29 were wounded
in the bombing of a union headquarters.
