<SECOND>BC-Totes-Germany,0172</SECOND>
<HEAD>Totes Buys German Umbrella Firm</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOVELAND, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Totes Inc., which makes and sells products
including umbrellas, boots and other footwear, says it is
purchasing a West German company which distributes umbrellas.
   Bradford Phillips, Totes' chief executive officer, said he
signed the agreement Tuesday in West Germany to buy Jagra-Haus
Gmbh. The German company will be renamed Totes Deutschland.
   Phillips refused to reveal the purchase price. He said it was a
cash transaction.
   Totes, based in Loveland, has annual sales of approximately $200
million.
   Phillips said Jagra-Haus will begin distributing Totes' full
line of umbrellas, boots and overshoes in early 1991. The German
firm will also distribute products of Totes' Chromatics division,
which makes lower-priced versions of Totes items sold under the
Chromatics name.
   Totes wants to expand Jagra-Haus' business territory beyond West
Germany, Phillips said.
   He said Totes may slightly increase its Loveland work force
beyond the current 550 people, as a result of the West German
acquisition.
