<FIRST>r f BC-Reuters     11-01 0121</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Reuters,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>General Manager of Reuters Resigns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Reuters Holdings PLC, a news and information
services company, said Wednesday its general manager, Michael
Reupke, has resigned to ``pursue other interests.''
   Reupke, 52, was appointed general manager in May. He previously
was editor-in-chief, a post he assumed in 1978.
   Reupke's responsibilities as general manager, traditionally the
second in command to Chairman and Chief Executive Glen Renfrew,
will be assumed by two people, Reuters said.
   One is Patrick Mannix, formerly international technical manager,
who was named a director of group quality programs and to
membership in the company's executive committee, effective
immediately.
   The other is Peter Holland, formerly deputy general manager, who
was appointed director of corporate affairs, effective immediately.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
