<HEAD>Major Newspaper Closings in the '80s</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Herald Examiner</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of the major afternoon daily newspapers to close
in recent years:
   The Miami News, 1989.
   The Baltimore News American, 1986.
   Memphis Press-Scimitar, 1983.
   The Cleveland Press, 1982.
   The Bulletin of Philadelphia, 1982.
   The Washington Star, 1982.
   Others have merged with morning newspapers with a common owner,
or switched to morning publication.
